<subSubSection id="2B916550A214FF90FB880C866466FCFE" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph id="633436DBA214FF91FB880C8661A6FA57" blockId="0.[910,1351,1384,1438]" box="[1072,1188,1415,1438]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
(
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA214FF91FB800C866199FA57" box="[1080,1179,1415,1438]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Figs 1–9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633436DBA214FF91FCEE0CC466D6F8E6" blockId="0.[816,1444,1477,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="51FFEAC9A214FF91FCEE0CC466E4FA13" bold="true" box="[854,998,1477,1498]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Description</emphasis>
. (Male). In the key to the males of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="A48B4D58A214FF91FC160CE5612EFA30" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[942,1068,1508,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51FFEAC9A214FF91FC160CE5612EFA30" box="[942,1068,1508,1529]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation id="071A4B2AA214FF91FC800F0266CDF9D0" author="Disney" box="[824,975,1539,1561]" firstAuthor="Disney" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref5836" refString="Disney, R. H. L. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8): 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
), with constant intermediates between choices, it runs to couplets 192, 200, 242 lead 2, 211, 213 and 220 lead 1. All options are excluded, along with subsequently added species running to these couplets, by details of the hypopygium along with features such as only 2 notopleural bristles and/or all brown legs and/or a longer costal index. In Borgmeir’s (1966) key to Nearctic Group VIII it runs to couplet 11 lead 2, but is likewise excluded. It fails to key out in the rest of the world’s fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633436DBA214FF90FCEE0E386466FCFE" blockId="0.[816,1444,1477,1901]" lastBlockId="1.[144,771,180,1040]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="51FFEAC9A214FF91FCEE0E386690F887" bold="true" box="[854,914,1849,1870]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Male</emphasis>
. Note, the front legs are missing in the only specimen available. Frons as 
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA214FF91FB160E5661FBF8A5" box="[1198,1273,1879,1901]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, without fine microtrichia. Cheek with 4 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, without SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FDB909F36740FECE" box="[513,578,242,264]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, the labella lacking short spinules below. Thorax brown, with 3 notopleural bristles, with no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron bare (
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FEC9084E64B7FEAC" box="[369,437,335,357]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites and venter as 
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FDAB088C6757FE6B" box="[531,597,397,419]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, the latter with small hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FD2408AD6602FE0B" box="[668,768,428,450]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Figs 5–7</figureCitation>
. Legs yellowish brown to dusky yellow. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.61 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur about as long as those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FDC80B2967B7FDF6" box="[624,693,552,575]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with at most a dozen only moderately differentiat- ed posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation id="FBB02A5EA215FF90FDE20B876798FD55" box="[602,666,646,668]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="2.[144,212,1859,1876]" captionTargetBox="[150,1439,738,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[589,1000,1063,1360]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–9. Megaselia aliusalius Disney, sp. nov. male. 1 – frons; 2 – antennae palps and proboscis; 3 – side of thorax; 4 – abdomen; 5 – left face of hypopygium; 6 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 7 – right face of hypopygium; 8 – hind femur and tibia; 9 – basal part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3776726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3776726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="A4739B3EA215FF90FD1A0B876601FD52" box="[674,771,646,668]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="1.06">1.06 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.39. Costal ratios with 1 clearly longer than 2+3 and 2 longer than 3. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="A4739B3EA215FF90FD020BC56601FD10" box="[698,771,708,729]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" unit="m" value="0.11">0.11 m</quantity>
long. Vein 3 hair 
<quantity id="A4739B3EA215FF90FEEB0BE264EFFD31" box="[339,493,739,760]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="0.025" valueMax="0.03" valueMin="0.02">0.02–0.03 mm</quantity>
long. 3 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity id="A4739B3EA215FF90FEC50A0364DEFCDE" box="[381,476,770,791]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
